import(std.error.assertion)
""
An [assertion](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Assertion_(software_development));
it should be given as its argument a predicate that should always evaluate to
true (i.e., an invariant). Will raise an `error.assertion` if `cond` is false.
""
pub fn assert(boolean cond, string message)
		if !cond error.assertion().raise(message)
